# 🖨️ Thermal Printer Service

A lightweight Node.js service to handle printing to a thermal receipt printer. This service is designed to run locally and listen on port `7001`.

## 🔧 Features

- ESC/POS command support
- Dynamic printer detection (default or by keyword)
- Auto-cut support
- REST API to trigger printing
- Logs success or failure of print jobs

## 📦 Requirements

- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- A thermal printer installed on the local machine (e.g., RP3160)

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/mhdyaseen8841/thermal_printer_service.git
cd thermal_printer_service

